        "timestamp": "2018-08-14 11:26:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI would expect the init behavior to be independent of which cloud it is running on when  we run a rancher based deployment.\n\nI usually see the same behavior whether I run on VMware, Azure or AWS.\nThere is mitigation if I increase the # and size of the cluster VMs as well as network bandwidth 10+ Gbps\nAlso note there are 2 timing profiles - whether or not the local docker image repo has been filled for that day\n\nI assume your deployment profile is Rancher 1.6.14, Docker 17.03, helm 2.8.2 on Azure",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
